BT /F1 10 Tf 54 690.2 Td (One day, a new student arrived at school. His name was Omar, and he was shy and quiet.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 676.2 Td (Some kids ignored him. Others whispered about his accent. Omar sat alone at lunch, staring) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 662.2 Td (at his food.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 648.2 Td (Zara watched him and immediately thought: 'How would I feel on my first day at a new) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 634.2 Td (school with no friends?') Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 620.2 Td (She knew the answer. Lonely. Scared. Invisible. She walked straight over to his table.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 606.2 Td ('Hi Omar! I am Zara. Want to sit with us? We have an empty spot and my friend Malik tells) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 592.2 Td (the funniest jokes.') Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 568.4 Td ([Illustration: Zara walking confidently over to the new boy Omar who sits alone, reaching) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 554.4 Td (out her hand, other kids at her table waving welcomingly, Omar looking surprised and) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 540.4 Td (hopeful]) Tj ET
