BT /F1 10 Tf 54 690.2 Td (Omar's face lit up. 'Really? You want me to sit with you?') Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 676.2 Td ('Of course!' Zara smiled. She remembered how Deepa had felt when someone finally noticed) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 662.2 Td (her. She remembered what it was like to feel included.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 648.2 Td (By the end of lunch, Omar was laughing at Malik's jokes, sharing stories about his old) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 634.2 Td (country, and looking like he belonged.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 620.2 Td ('Thank you, Zara,' Omar said quietly as the bell rang. 'I was so scared nobody would talk) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 606.2 Td (to me.') Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 592.2 Td ('I know that feeling,' Zara said. 'And I never want anyone to feel it if I can help.') Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 568.4 Td ([Illustration: Omar laughing at the lunch table with Zara and her friends, completely) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 554.4 Td (included and happy, a transformation from lonely to belonging in one lunch period]) Tj ET
